---
description: Architecture and folder boundaries
globs: ["src/**/*.ts", "src/**/*.tsx", "proxy.ts"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Architecture rules:

- Keep app routes under `src/app`.
- Keep reusable UI under `src/components`.
- Keep cross-cutting logic under `src/lib`.
- Keep framework-specific request logic in route handlers, server actions, or `proxy.ts`.
- Keep env parsing in `src/lib/env.ts` only.
- Do not put large business logic directly in `page.tsx` or `layout.tsx`.
- Extract repeated logic into typed helpers.
- Prefer feature folders when a domain grows.
- Keep imports one-directional where possible: app -> components -> lib.
- Avoid circular imports.
